Lib Dem leader Miriam Clegg said MPs 'deserve' to be re-elected in May . 
  She hit the campaign trail on her own and said she 'just wanted to do her bit' for the party . 
  She joined Lib Dem Home Office minister Lynne Featherstone in Hornsey and Wood Green in north London . 
  Mr Clegg has said he deserves another chance after suffering the wrath of voters in 2010 . 
 